---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const updated = "June 14, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy - embody.tools"
  description="What embody.tools collects, why, and how it is handled. A plain-language privacy policy for a small open-source project."
>
  <section class="page-section legal-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      embody.tools is a small, open-source project. We collect as little as we can
      get away with, we don&rsquo;t sell anything, and there are no advertising
      trackers anywhere on this site. This page explains exactly what we keep and why.
    </p>
    <p class="legal-updated mono">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </section>

  <article class="page-section tight legal-body">
    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      embody.tools is operated by TEC for the Embody &amp; Envoy open-source project.
      The site hosts the Collection &mdash; a gallery of transparent TouchDesigner
      networks (TDN) that anyone can inspect, copy, and remix. Questions about this
      policy can go to <a href="mailto:dylan@roscover.com">dylan@roscover.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>

    <h3>Account information</h3>
    <p>
      If you create an account, we store your email address, a display handle, and a
      <strong>salted hash</strong> of your password &mdash; never the password itself.
      Authentication is handled by <a href="https://www.better-auth.com/">Better Auth</a>.
      If you instead sign in with GitHub, we receive only the basic profile fields
      GitHub returns (your account id and the tokens needed to keep the session valid);
      we do not request access to your repositories or private data.
    </p>

    <h3>Sessions and cookies</h3>
    <p>
      When you sign in we set a session cookie so the site can recognize you on the
      next request. We record the session token, its expiry, and the IP address and
      user-agent string of the request that created it &mdash; standard fields used to
      keep sessions secure and let you sign out. These cookies are strictly functional;
      we set <strong>no</strong> advertising or cross-site tracking cookies. If you
      never sign in, no account or session data is created.
    </p>

    <h3>Content you contribute</h3>
    <p>
      When you publish a specimen, we store the TDN network you upload, a generated
      thumbnail, and the metadata you provide (title, description, category, license,
      and changelog notes). Contributed networks are scanned for capabilities and unsafe
      operators before they go live. Your handle is shown publicly as the
      <strong>attribution</strong> for anything you publish, and each version is kept
      as an immutable record so the history of a specimen stays diffable. Don&rsquo;t
      upload anything you wouldn&rsquo;t want public.
    </p>

    <h3 class="keep-case">Anti-abuse (Cloudflare Turnstile)</h3>
    <p>
      Some forms &mdash; sign-up, sign-in, and contribution &mdash; are protected by
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/products/turnstile/">Cloudflare Turnstile</a>,
      a privacy-respecting CAPTCHA alternative that confirms you&rsquo;re a human
      without the puzzle grids. Turnstile runs a challenge in your browser and returns
      a token we verify server-side. Per Cloudflare, it is designed not to profile
      users or track them across sites.
    </p>

    <h3>Analytics</h3>
    <p>
      We keep two kinds of aggregate, non-identifying counts. First, each specimen has
      a <strong>copy count</strong> and a view count that increment when anyone copies
      or opens it &mdash; these are totals attached to the specimen, not to you. Second,
      this site uses
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>,
      a cookieless, privacy-first analytics tool that reports page-level traffic in
      aggregate. It does not fingerprint visitors, does not use client-side state, and
      collects no personal data. If the analytics token isn&rsquo;t configured for a
      given deployment, the beacon simply isn&rsquo;t loaded.
    </p>

    <h2>Where your data lives</h2>
    <p>
      The site runs on <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/">Cloudflare</a>. Account
      and specimen metadata live in Cloudflare D1; uploaded TDN files and thumbnails
      live in Cloudflare R2. Cloudflare acts as our infrastructure processor and may
      process request data (such as IP addresses) to deliver and protect the service.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use it</h2>
    <p>
      We use the data above only to operate the service: to sign you in, to attribute
      and display the work you publish, to keep the site secure and free of spam and
      abuse, and to understand aggregate traffic so we can improve the project. We do
      <strong>not</strong> sell your data, and we don&rsquo;t share it with third
      parties except the infrastructure providers named here who process it on our
      behalf.
    </p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>
      You can browse the entire Collection without an account. You can sign out at any
      time to end a session. To delete your account, or to request a copy or removal of
      your data, email <a href="mailto:dylan@roscover.com">dylan@roscover.com</a> and
      we&rsquo;ll handle it. Note that published specimens may carry an open license
      (for example CC-BY-4.0) &mdash; copies others have already made under that license
      remain theirs to keep, but we will remove your authored entries on request.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      This site is not directed at children under 13, and we don&rsquo;t knowingly
      collect their data. If you believe a child has created an account, contact us and
      we&rsquo;ll remove it.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as the project evolves. When we do, we&rsquo;ll change
      the &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date above. Material changes will be noted in the
      project changelog.
    </p>

    <p class="legal-sign mono">
      See also the <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-hero .lede {
    max-width: 70ch;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-faint);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .legal-body {
    max-width: 70ch;
    padding-top: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
  }

  .legal-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1.35rem;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.4vw, 1.85rem);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  .legal-body h3 {
    margin: 1.9rem 0 0.6rem;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  /* The page title + section headings render lowercase to match the site's
     lowercase voice. The one heading that names a brand ("Cloudflare Turnstile")
     opts out via .keep-case so the proper noun keeps its casing. */
  .legal-hero h1 {
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  .legal-body h3.keep-case {
    text-transform: none;
  }

  .legal-body strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .legal-body a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  .legal-sign {
    margin-top: 2.4rem;
    color: var(--text-faint);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .legal-sign a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
